properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 3 at 6:10PM CST until January 4 at 12:00AM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Slick Travel Across North-Central and Northeast Iowa This
Evening...

.A slow-moving band of moderate to occasionally heavy snow
continues to pivot over portions of north-central and northeast
Iowa this evening. County dispatch centers have reported several
accidents and slide-offs due to snow-covered, slick roads. An
additional 1 to 2 inches of snowfall is expected before the
accumulating snow drifts southward by late evening. Visibility has
been poor within the heaviest snowfall, down to a half mile at
times. If traveling this evening, be alert for slippery road
conditions and poor visibility. Slow down and allow extra time to
reach your destination.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to two inches.

* WHERE...Portions of north central and northeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...County dispatch centers have reported
several vehicle accidents and slide-offs this evening. Roads are
snow-covered and slick. Visibility is also poor within the band
of heaviest snow, down to a half mile at times.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT
